 other during that time and in that location. However, no specific details about the nature of their interactions or the reasons for them are given.'], 'Query': 'default rules, The statements provided outline a hypothetical scenario set in St Andrews, Scotland, in the year 1546, involving two individuals, James Moffat and Elizabeth Lindsay. The text suggests several plausible reasons why these two individuals might interact with each other during that time and in that location. However, no specific details about the nature of their interactions or the reasons for them are given.'}}, 'resolve': {'__act__': {'Summary': 'Event: In the bright morning light illuminating the ruins of St Andrews Cathedral, James Moffat strolled through the narrow, cobblestone streets. The scholar from St Mary\'s College pondered deep philosophical thoughts when he noticed Elizabeth Lindsay approaching him. Elizabeth, his university mate from St Salvator\'s College, carried a troubled expression.\n\nUpon seeing Elizabeth, James, who was known for his resiliency and empathy, offered a warm, inviting smile and greeted her, “Good morning, Elizabeth.”\n\nJames immediately sensed Elizabeth\'s distress. He moved closer and asked, "Elizabeth, is everything alright? You seem troubled."\n\nElizabeth looked at James, her eyes filled with a mix of thoughts and worries. “James, I was coming to find you. There\'s been a disturbance at St Salvator\'s College.”\n\nJames\' curiosity and concern were piqued. He gestured toward a nearby bench beside the cathedral ruins and suggested, “Let\'s sit down. Tell me what happened.”\n\nHe listened attentively as Elizabeth explained, “There\'s been word a heated debate among our scholars. Tempers are getting out of hand, and I worry that if left unchecked, it might lead to a more significant issue.”\n\nSensing the gravity of the situation, James stood and said, “We must go there and lend our guidance. How do you think the current tensions can guide us toward greater 